      <akn:section eId="sec_28:3_304">
        <akn:num>28:3-304</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Overdue instrument.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:3-304_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>An instrument payable on demand becomes overdue at the earliest of the following times:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:3-304_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>With respect to an instrument payable at a definite time the following rules apply:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:3-304_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Unless the due date of principal has been accelerated, an instrument does not become overdue if there is default in payment of interest but no default in payment of principal.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
